Congratulations to President-elect Joe Biden & Vice President-elect Kamala Harris! We have our work cut out for us and the road to recovery is long but they have a plan to lead us to a brighter tomorrow. Today the American people won. Today we celebrate this historic victory.

It is my honor to accept another term to represent CT-3. Thank you to the voters for your confidence in me to our campaign & volunteers and to my family. The people of CT said Yes to bold actions for the future & I am ready to work for big results. Thank you for your support. https://t.co/gNMgjICDO7

I am honored to accept the Hearst CT Media Editorial Board’s endorsement for my re-election. They recognize that my priorities in Congress are the issues that matter most to working families. I will continue my fight to ensure the health and economic security of working people. https://t.co/5m27YKcMel
New Haven pizza.   That’s it. That’s the tweet.  #CT03debate #Vote2020
My life’s work has been centered on workers’ rights working families pay equity paid leave and a tax system that works for the middle class. #CT03debate #Vote2020

Trade agreements should be centered on workers. They should benefit the economy but protect the worker. I have led trade negotiations for the new NAFTA to make sure there were labor protections environmental protections and to stop jobs from going overseas. #CT03debate #Vote2020
People fought and died for the right to vote. Vote by mail is safe. Absentee voting is safe. Don’t be afraid to vote. #CT03debate #Vote2020

I am a daughter of an immigrant. My roots are deep in the Wooster Square Community. I am proud of my Italian heritage and I understand how representation is vital to immigrant communities. #CT03debate #Vote2020
We need to be on a path to universal healthcare. #CT03debate #Vote2020

I am proud to have introduced legislation to create a $50 billion child care stabilization fund. This would provide grant funding to child care providers to stabilize the child care sector and support providers to safely reopen and operate. #CT03debate #Vote2020

We all want to see our children go back to school. I am concerned that they are losing opportunities. But we have to make sure we have a safe environment for them and for our teachers. #CT03debate #Vote2020

When we get the coronavirus under control we can get our economy under control. We must get the people back on their feet and continue to build up a strong infrastructure and manufacturing base. #CT03debate #Vote2020
